Package: statascii
Type: Package
Title: Create Stata-like ASCII tables in R
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Gustavo Velásquez
Maintainer: Gustavo Velásquez <gvelasq2@users.noreply.github.com>
Description: The `statascii()` function is an adapted version of `asciify()` by @gavinsimpson. It creates Stata-like ASCII tables in the R console, including right-aligned text, Stata-like padding, various Stata table formats (`oneway`, `twoway`, and `summary`), and Unicode box drawing characters.
License: MIT
LazyData: TRUE
URL: http://github.com/gvelasq2/statascii
BugReports: http://github.com/gvelasq2/statascii/issues
